Forming the block low-rank preconditioner with shared basis.After obtaining the new shared basis \(\bm{B}_{t}\), we compute the block-dependent \(k\)-by-\(k\) coefficient matrices by

\[\tilde{\bm{R}}_{t}^{(i)}=(\bm{B}_{t})^{T}\bm{M}_{t}^{(i)}\bm{B}_{t},\]

which is optimal in terms of minimizing the Frobenius norm reconstruction error for each block. Following the literature of frequent direction approaches [14], we remove the smallest eigenvalue to enable better online updates:

\[\bm{R}_{t}^{(i)}=\tilde{\bm{R}}_{t}^{(i)}-\sigma_{\text{min}}(\tilde{\bm{R}}_{ t}^{(i)})\bm{I}.\]

To account for the missing mass in the low-rank approximation, we track a scalar value for each block using the recurrence relation:

\[\rho_{t}^{(i)}=\rho_{t-1}^{(i)}+\|\bm{M}_{t}^{(i)}-\bm{B}_{t}\bm{R}_{t}^{(i)}( \bm{B}_{t})^{T}\|,\]

which can be efficiently computed using power iteration. Finally, to derive the update direction \(\bm{u}_{t}^{(i)}\), we compute

\[\bm{u}_{t}^{(i)}= -(\bm{B}_{t}\bm{R}_{t}^{(i)}(\bm{B}_{t})^{T}+(\rho_{t}^{(i)}+ \epsilon)\bm{I})^{-1/2}\bm{g}_{t}^{(i)}\] (6) \[= -\bm{B}_{t}(\bm{R}_{t}^{(i)}+(\rho_{t}^{(i)}+\epsilon)\bm{I})^{-1 /2}(\bm{B}_{t})^{T}\bm{g}_{t}^{(i)}+(\rho_{t}^{(i)}+\epsilon)^{-1/2}\bm{B}_{t} (\bm{B}_{t})^{T}\bm{g}_{t}^{(i)}-(\rho_{t}^{(i)}+\epsilon)^{-1/2}\bm{g}_{t}^{( i)}.\]

Detailed derivations can be found in Appendix 6.5. Here we follow Shampoo [16] to add the \(\epsilon\bm{I}\) before taking the matrix square root, which is slightly different from the Adagrad formulation shown in (1).

